nodes.bodyText: There really isn't a point in having this override method if all it does is call the super.
I'd be interested in adding some unit tests for this class down the line. I think some of the regular expressions used here might be a little too loose and open the possibility for false negatives.

nodes.bodyText: I'm confused by this one - the point of it being a ResponseFullExpectation object is because the search location is the full response, and always will be the full response. An expectation that searches somewhere else would be a different type of expectation.
it was in because of a method in JwtApiExpectations and that method wasn't actually used - both being removed with issue 10532

After more digging (and stopping/starting my eclipse to see that the method in JwtApiExpectations was needed), I can't remove this - I need to create a JwtTimeClaimExpectation with these parms, that expectation extends JwtApiExpectation which in turn extends ResponseFullExpectation.  I can't access the contructor without this and the one in JwtApiExpectations being defined.  (I need a JwtTimeClaimExpectation so that I get the override validation method that does special time comparisons in the full response).  The constructors aren't inherited, so I need each method used in each of the classes.
These shouldn't be here and should be covered by the bnd.bnd file.
